      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HANDS ON TINA (7) showed good early speed last start and led throughout to win for the first time by 7 lengths at this track over 388m (22.38). Will break from a wide draw. Rates on top again. RUBY TANUKI (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing seventh (30.83) in a Grade 5 at The Gardens. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can figure in the finish. BIGBAD MAISIE (2) has been a little hard to follow, finishing out of the placings latest but was in winning form two back scoring in a Maiden at this track. Good beginner and aided by a handy draw. Can turn it around this time. SAMJAI (3) is one of the chances after a minor prize from this draw last time.",
